

**Python GIT Training \- Basic**

**Python GIT Training Course Package (48 Hours)**

![][image1]

**Course Title:**

**Python Programming for Developers – Aligned with Python Institute Certifications**

**Course Duration:**

**48 Hours** (Instructor-led, Hands-on)

**Course Description:**

Python is one of the most in-demand and versatile programming languages, widely used across web development, automation, AI, and Android development (via Kivy or APIs). This 48-hour course offers hands-on programming experience from basics to intermediate concepts, aligning with the Python Institute’s PCAP certification. Students will build real Python applications and gain a solid foundation for careers in software and mobile app development.

**Course Objectives:**

Upon successful completion, students will be able to:

* Set up Python and develop applications using Python 3\.

* Perform operations on data types and structures.

* Implement decision-making and loops.

* Use functions, classes, and modules.

* Handle files and exceptions.

* Apply object-oriented principles.

* Prepare for the Python Institute’s PCEP/PCAP exams.

**Target Audience:**

* Aspiring programmers and developers.

* Android/web developers using Python for backend logic.

* QA testers and automation engineers.

* IT professionals aiming to get Python Institute certified.

**Prerequisites:**

* Basic computing knowledge.

* Optional: Previous experience with any programming language.

**Technical Setup (Lab Requirements):**

* Windows 10/11 64-bit

* Python 3.x (latest stable release)

* VirtualBox \+ Lubuntu 24.04 VM (as per provided materials)

* VS Code or PyCharm (optional)

* Internet access for package installations


  ![][image2]

**Course Outline (Modules)**

| Module | Topic |
| :---- | :---- |
| **1** | Setting Up Python and Creating a Simple Application |
| **2** | Processing Simple Data Types (Strings, Numbers) |
| **3** | Working with Data Structures (Lists, Tuples, Sets, Dicts) |
| **4** | Writing Conditional Statements and Loops |
| **5** | Defining and Using Functions, Classes, and Modules |
| **6** | File and Directory Operations (Read/Write Files) |
| **7** | Exception Handling (Built-in and Custom) |
| **8** | Capstone Project & Certification Exam Prep |

  * PCAP™ – Certified Associate in Python Programming
